<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871124-0135 </DOCNO><HL> GM Sells U.K. Truck Plant</HL><DD> 11/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> DETROIT  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Motors Corp. said it completed the sale of its Bedford heavy-duty truck plant in Dunstable, England, to AWD Ltd., a newly formed company headed by British investor David Brown.    GM wouldn't disclose the terms of the transaction, which was announced in September. The Bedford operation accounted for most of GM's $340 million loss in Europe last year.    Mr. Brown said he hopes to expand the number of export and military vehicles produced. The current 1,100 employees will retain their jobs at the plant. </TEXT></DOC>